<br>
It's always pissed me off when getting a group together to toddle off to a camp and have someone leave in 10 or 15 minutes to go raid.<br>
<br>
What the @#%$ were you doing joining a group when you have to go raid in 10 minutes?  Why aren't you moving your pathetic arse to the raid site?  Why are you @#%$ with 5 other poeple who are expecting to settle in for some xp, only to have your sorry arse bow out for SOMETHING YOU KNEW ABOUT BEFORE YOU STARTED.<br>
<br>
In LDoN it's even worse.  3 times it's happened to the group I was in for LDoN... halfway into the dungeon &quot;oh, I have to leave for a raid.&quot;  Here's a clue for you hard of thinking raid monkeys:  It takes 2 hours to run through an LDoN dungeon... if it's 5 PM and you have a raid at 5:30 or 6 PM, you are a whipped cream asshat with a steaming turd on top if you join an LDoN group, and just a steaming turd (no whipped cream) if you join a regular group without informing them.<br>
<br>
Ordinarily, I'd complain that it happens that most of the cretins who have done this lately have been Fury's Edge/lings, but I'll spare them the brunt of this because Soulthirst stayed to the end of an LDoN group yesterday even though he had a raid and based on what I've seen, that appeared to take some guts and showed respect for the other people in the group.  So I give a little rave to Soulthirst!<br>
<br>
The funny thing is, grouping right to the last second before a raid probably makes that person late for the raid too and piss the raid people off.  Presumably that makes the people who do it get a second asshat.<br>
<br>
Now to calm down, I offer you Laura Prepon:<br>
