 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=demanimt>DemaniMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lonely in Kera Ridge</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/18/03 9:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1156.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: If you have to raid, don't @#%$ join an LDoN group</span><hr size=1> That seems about the norm so far Jordaan. People that are in raiding or even a semi-raid guild should have some idea of what time they usually start. However, there are also times when impromptu raids may be called. Things happen unfortunately. Perhaps it should be kept in mind what time you start looking for others to join you and if anyone from say, FE, Rev or Triune say yes...they MAY have to leave soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aelfgarraintree>AelfgarRaintree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 399<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/18/03 9:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1156.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: If you have to raid, don't @#%$ join an LDoN group</span><hr size=1> Jord, you are such spoiled a spolied little biatch. Try a few pick up groups with non-Triune/Rev/Fe/FEling/Lov level people, you won't do them in 40 minutes. (well, except for the slaughter missions, even NoI could do those quickly)<br>
<br>
Also try some groups with less than perfect set ups... some work awesome, some not so good.<br>
<br>
Mind you, I think every group I have been in that has failed (4 so far out of 14) failed for one of 2 reasons: BAD communication and BAD tactics. Mmm, what a good idea for a rant... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draxusmt>Draxus MT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giant Squishies in Rathe</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/18/03 10:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1156.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: If you have to raid, don't @#%$ join an LDoN group</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You don't want to risk your group getting broken up don't take folks from raiding crews into your LDoN group.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Here's a better idea, how about informing your group if you have any possibility of having to raid within the next two hours.  It's a simple matter of common courtesy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Normal adventures, especially those where u kill an X number of mobs can be done in about 40 minutes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That depends on your role in the group.  If you're not the puller, then you likely have minimal influence on the pace of the group.  I am generally puller for my groups, so I get to set a brisk pace through the dungeons &amp; 40 mins is pretty easy.  When im playing my BST, however, I am usually at the mercy of whoever else is pulling. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sasarella>Sasarella</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Riding the Planes</span><br>  Posts: 830<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/18/03 10:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1156.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: If you have to raid, don't @#%$ join an LDoN group</span><hr size=1> Neh, I don't think Jord is spoiled. He's just careful who he groups with. While on a good FE run we can do an adventure in 25-30 min, at best I've had some pretty nice pick up groups of Non-Uber guild folks that knew what they were doing and we plowed through there in 40 min or less.<br>
<br>
Its all on how well you work together, know your class, and how little you doddle around.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bwahthebard>Bwah the Bard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/18/03 10:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1156.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: If you have to raid, don't @#%$ join an LDoN group</span><hr size=1> It strikes me as odd that 'informing a group you may have to raid soon' is a good thing, when you shouldn't be joining that group in the first place if that's so! Just join a regular XP group where you can easily draft in a replacement if necessary. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qrgauthil>Qrgauthil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Looting Highpass</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/18/03 10:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1156.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: If you have to raid, don't @#%$ join an LDoN group</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Not really... Normal adventures, especially those where u kill an X number of mobs can be done in about 40 minutes.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, it is usually done in less, but if you're planning you should factor the max 30 min to get there and 90 min for hte mission:  2 hours.<br>
<br>
Sure, realistically, it's 5-10 min to get there and 40-60 min for the mission, or just over 1 hour.  I think anyone who has 1 hour to play and joins an LDoN group is an inconsiderate idiot though.  There are a billion things that could go wrong, no matter how uber your group is.  For every mission that is done in 30 minutes, I bet there are 50 or more that take 80 minutes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;I have to leave for a raid&quot; is another way of saying &quot;omg how did I end up in this lame a$$ group.. mmm how can I politely get out of it..&quot;<br>
